webwork-tex.statement:
\leavevmode\\\relax
Match the parametric equations with the graphs labeled A - F. As always, you may click on the thumbnail image to produce a larger image in a new window (sometimes exactly on top of the old one).
\par
\par\begin{enumerate} \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}1.] \(x = \cos t, y = \sin t, z = \ln t\) \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}2.] \(x = \cos t, y = \sin t, z = \sin 5t\) \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}3.] \(x = \sin 3t \cos t, y = \sin 3t \sin t, z = t\) \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}4.] \(x=\cos 4t, y = t, z = \sin 4t\) \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}5.] \(x = t^2 - 2, y = t^3, z = t^4 + 1\) \item[\mbox{\parbox[t]{3ex}{\hrulefill}}6.] \(x = t, y = 1/(1+t^2), z = t^2\) \end{enumerate}
